Package nbt.tag

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TagOperation
    Functional interface that defines a operation that is used to search for tags that fit certain conditions.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ByteArrayTag
    A tag that is designed to hold an array of bytes and may have a name associated with it.
    ByteTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single byte and a name that may be associated with it.
    CompoundTag
    A tag that contains an unspecified number of tags that are guaranteed to contain a name and a payload corresponding to the type of that tag.
    DoubleTag
    A tag is designed to hold a single double and a name that may be associated with it.
    EndTag
    A tag that is designed to signal the end of a compound tag.
    FloatTag
    A tag is designed to hold a single float and a name that may be associated with it.
    IntArrayTag
    A tag that is designed to hold an array of ints and may have a name associated with it.
    IntTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single int and a name that may be associated with it.
    ListTag<T extends Tag>
    A tag is designed to a hold a fixed number of tag payloads with a specific tag type.
    LongArrayTag
    A tag that is designed to hold an array of longs and may have a name associated with it.
    LongTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single long and a name that may be associated with it.
    ShortTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single short and a name that may be associated with it.
    StringTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single string and a name that may be associated with it.
    Tag<T>
    An abstract class that outlines the basic fields and methods that all tags must contain.
    TagIterator
    An iterator that is designed to loop through the contained tags within compound and list tags.
